In this case it is important not to lose potential customer who will buy a personal loan, with a type two error(false negatives-potential customers who are being overlooked) being 16 i.e.,1.6% out of the 1000 customers in the testing dataset.¶

The accuracy is 96% and the precision for potential customers is 96% with a recall of 59%. In this case it is important not to lose potential customer who will buy a personal loan, with a type two error(false negatives-potential customers who are being overlooked) being 4 i.e., 0.4% out of the 1000 customers in the testing dataset. That is good with capturing as much potential customers(false negative being the lowest) as possible.¶

Logistic Regression has a Recall of 60%, Precision of 85%, Accuracy of 95% and the Area under Curve is 95%¶

Naive Bayes has a Recall of 54%, Precision of 42%, Accuracy of 88% and the Area under Curve is 91%¶

KNN has a Recall of 59%, Precision of 96%, Accuracy of 96% and the Area under Curve is 91%¶

As per my analysis, KNN is the better method that has to be adopted in order to predict if a customer is potential to buy a personal loan as the type 2 error is low in it, precision is very high indicating the number of potential customers being overlooked low and also with a high accuracy of predicting potential customers who will a buy personal loan with 96%.¶
